5:
...So this is the village where your
former masters once lived.
9:
Yes. I am glad we were able to pay
our respects to their graves.
16:
Excellent form! As expected of
someone of your skill.
20:
...Murakumo has learned how to
smile with such kindness.
22:
It is quite strange. I can sense rage
from the boy.
25:
He is not Murakumo's master. He
does not desire to wield him.
28:
Despite everything, Murakumo can
offer up that smile. Do you know why?
32: I do not. I am sorry.
36:
You are a strange one as well,
always making that perplexed
expression.
41:
Will you not play with the other
children?
44:
Why? They're all happy already.
They don't care if I'm there or not.
46:
It's not fair. People like them deserve
to suffer too.
50:
She had a look in her eyes... Exactly
like the one our masters had...
56: You should do as you please.
60:
Even if I should turn into a vengeful
spirit once more?
65:
I will be there to stop you, should the
need arise. But who is to say that
outcome is guaranteed?
68:
Besides... You looked pained. I would
rather you did something instead of
standing idly by.
72:
A mirror? I don't remember us
having one.
76:
Manoka, spirit of the mirror, at your
service. Good evening, child.
79: Y-you're that weird lady from earlier!
82: Indeed. I have come to visit.
88:
Your gaze was filled with cold
disdain when you gazed upon me.
91:
Do you detest those who smile and
laugh along with others?
94:
I hate them all. They didn't do
anything to help when my mom was
sick!
97:
Would you like for them to suffer
with you?
100:
Should you wish it, we can unleash
untold destruction and trap them in
a bleak nightmare, until you have
had your fill.
106: No... I'm... It's me that I hate.
108:
I couldn't do anything for my mom
when she was suffering!
110:
She was in pain no matter what I
did. And now she'll never smile
again!
116: I failed to give a proper reflection.
122:
It is my role to reflect your greatest
wish.
128: She's smiling... She looks so happy...
140: Thank you for looking after me.
144:
...It was nothing. I am satisfied if you
are.
156:
I was surrounded by darkness. It was
all my existence ever amounted to.
159:
Yet in a brief moment, the darkness
parted to reveal a face.
161:
One with furrowed brows and
twisted into a perplexed expression.
167:
I found myself wishing for that
person to smile.
175:
And what do you wish of me? Do
you only seek my smile?
189: Oh, Murakumo. Is this what you felt?
192:
I have decided that I will continue to
journey alongside you all.
195:
As I would very much like to share a
meal with you as well.
207: As am I. It is heartening to see.
210: ...Do you want to play with us too?
213: Hehe, of course. What shall we do?
